<pdd-reason>Adapter layer from unified prompt source-set reports to named agentic checkup tools.</pdd-reason>
<pdd-interface>
{
  "type": "module",
  "module": {
    "classes": [
      {"name": "ToolResult", "kind": "dataclass"},
      {"name": "CheckupTool", "kind": "protocol"}
    ],
    "constants": [
      {"name": "ALL_TOOLS", "type": "dict[str, CheckupTool]"}
    ]
  }
}
</pdd-interface>
<pdd-dependency>checkup_prompt_main_python.prompt</pdd-dependency>

% Goal
Write `pdd/checkup_tools.py`.

% Requirements
- Expose deterministic tool adapters for lint, contract, coverage, gate, snapshot, and drift checks represented in `PromptSourceSetReport`.
- Tool extraction MUST reuse the already-built report; it must not rerun LLMs or mutate files.
- Tool results include status, skip reason where relevant, and the findings belonging to the tool.

<contract_rules>
R1 - Report adapter only
Tool extraction MUST be a read-only projection of `PromptSourceSetReport`.
</contract_rules>

% Deliverables
- Code: `pdd/checkup_tools.py`
